data.title: Home Page | PAWS Chicago
data.meta_description: PAWS Chicago is a national model in animal sheltering, committed to bringing an end to the killing of homeless cats and dogs.
data.text:
5K Walk/Run for Their Lives

The PAWS 5K raises critical funds and awareness for homeless pets. Plus, it’s a whole lot of fun! There are sponsor giveaways, a dog agility course, a doggy oasis with pools and dog spa services, a photo station and other fun photo ops, raffles, treats, and you'll meet tons of other pet lovers. Register now for the lowest prices of the year!

Clear the Shelters Adoption Event

Join PAWS Chicago for National Clear the Shelters Day. So many homeless pets are looking for loving families. Give these cats and dogs a second chance on Saturday, August 24, 11 a.m.–5 p.m. at the Pippen Fasseas Adoption Center. The adoption fee will be waived for select pets.

Angels with Tails Barrington

The event that launched PAWS Chicago’s lifesaving mission over 27 years ago is coming to Barrington. Please join us for Angels with Tails, a homeless pet adoption event for the whole community! Adoptable dogs, cats, puppies, and kittens will take over your favorite storefronts across downtown Barrington on Saturday, August 24, noon–4 p.m. No appointments are needed and the whole family is invited.

Pup Premiere Adoption Event

For one sparkling evening, furry stars from foster homes will make an appearance at the Pippen Fasseas Adoption Center to meet their adoring public on Saturday, August 31, 6–9 p.m. Usually, potential adopters meet foster pups one at a time and by appointment only. Take advantage of this opportunity to find your new best friend even faster.

Complete Your Home Adoption Event

Furnish your home and fill your heart all at the same time on Saturday, September 14. Adoptable dogs and cats will be available at Skokie, IL Walter E. Smithe Furniture & Design from noon–3 p.m.

Volunteer Open House

Interested in helping save the lives of homeless cats and dogs in Chicago? Join PAWS Chicago at the upcoming Volunteer Open House on Tuesday, September 17, and Thursday, September 19, from 1–5 p.m. at the Pippen Fasseas Adoption Center.

Kitten Season is Here!

Kitten season is officially back and so is our Kitten Season Challenge! This year, PAWS Chicago is on a mission to find homes for at least 350 kittens. Click to learn how you can help!

Virtual + In-Person Training

Train your pup from the comfort of your home or at our Lincoln Park Adoption Center. Small class sizes ensure an environment conducive to learning. Sign up now!

Donate Supplies On Our Wishlist

Help us stretch our dollars by donating supplies. New and most gently used items are greatly appreciated. We do have limited storage space, so we have put together a list of the items we need the most.

Junior Rescuers Youth Tours

Join us at 10:30 a.m. on the second Saturday of every month for a tour of the Pippen Fasseas Adoption Center. This is the perfect opportunity for Scout troops, school groups, families, and kids to get a first-hand look at what it means to give homeless pets a second chance. Click to register!
